ensus is starting to rise that a few 60 wizards are almost as important as a 60 warrior (main tank).  I personally dont know if I can believe this or not.  I know lures are very powerful spells and such, and GB and DB even more so, but really how many casts can a wizard get off before going oom.  Even if its on their bind point and they die FM naked is usually about 50% or less then fully clothed.<br>
<br>
That being said most I talk to still seem to insist that 3-5 60 wizards on any high end encounter are really important.  Im not denying that just trying to see how so.<br>
<br>
Any you wizards want to give examples pre 60, pre DB/GB and post GB/DB damage?<br>
<br>
D<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upsychodelia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Psychodelia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/30/01 2:33:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.erowid.org/chemicals/lsd/images/archive/lsd_blotter_chill_sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards and the end game</span><hr size=1> Well, I do know 60 wiz with bane spells are vital to the high end game because I feel far more guilty not being able to contribute with them more often.<br>
<br>
Theres a couple things here id like to mention that might fill in some spaces for you.<br>
<br>
Dragonsbane does 2000 instant damage on all LORD/LADY ancient dragons.<br>
<br>
Dragonsbane has VERY low taunt.<br>
<br>
The recast time is only 2 seconds.<br>
<br>
It hits from far away.<br>
<br>
A 60 wizard can cast anywhere from 8-10 before going oom. However, necros, mod rods, clarity, any manaregen can boost this number greatly.  Its possible for one wizard, let alone a few, to do an astronomical amount of damage very easily and very quickly.<br>
<br>
Its the reward for a very difficult quest.(highly rare spawn)<br>
<br>
Sunstrike is also very useful on many high level encounters when coupled with brainbite.<br>
<br>
Some well equipped 60 wizards have items which cast direct damage, which solves any oom/useless problems.<br>
<br>
<br>
I hope that helps some.<br>
<br>
<br>
