 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uyurimaru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yurimaru</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=" http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/4/01 1:52:20 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.360d.com/vf2/gif/kage/newkage.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards and the end game</span><hr size=1> I would say there is a place for wizards in the high end game.  Its called translocate =P  j/k !<br>
<br>
Psycho is right in saying that a wizard can do a phenominal amount of damage quickly with the bane line of spells.  They used to be instant recast, but were recently changed to have a 5 second recast delay, but it could be said that the longer recast delay helps reduce over aggro'ing.  They are completly unresistable vs. mobs you can cast them on which means you dont have to be in melee range to hit.  They also have very low aggro attached to them which is good because 2000 DD would tend to upset big mobs very quickly.  I can generally cast 8 to 10 per encounter before using up all my mana.  Things like mod rods, necro dumps, mana robes, and the full suite of mana regen buffs can really help to overcome the mana problem.<br>
<br>
To illustrate the importance I'll use the example of Velketor the Sorceror.  One particular encounter with Velk saw us with one level 60 warrior, 5 60th wizards, and 29 others.  In this encounter I hit Velk for 22k damage via Hsagra's Wrath (GB) and the other wizards involved did a similar amount of damage i.e. Kurven did 18k. The spell damage from the wizards alone accounted for the significant portion of Velks life and was perhaps the reason we were able to win that fight.<br>
<br>
The bane line of spells aren't the only saving grace of the wizard class either.  In a fight with the Statue of Rallos Zek I was forced to use lure of ice (825 DD) as it was the only consistent hitting spell.  I successfully landed 22 lure of ice for a total of 18150 damage and I lived the whole fight.  While that damage doesnt hold a candle to rogues it is certainly a decent contribution and decidedly more than a paladin or mage would do.<br>
<br>
In addition to the lure line of spells other spells such as sunstrike (1615 DD) and Ice spear of solist (4:1 ratio 1200 DD) can really help out in high end encounters where resistances arent as much of an issue (Gorenaire, VP dragons, Dozekar etc.) <p><p align=left><b>Yurimaru Manaburn </b><br>
<font color=lightblue> 60th High Sorcerer </font> <br>
<font color=lightblue> Brell Serilis</font> <br>
<a href=http://pub32.ezboard.com/benshadowed><font color=lightblue>  Enshadowed</font></a><br>
